definitions: (of a gas or its container) not having raised pressure that is produced or maintained artificially

examples.text: in unpressurized air, the vapor levels were too low to trigger a serious fire

shortDefinitions: (of gas or its container) not having raised pressure that is produced or maintained artificially

definitions: (of an aircraft cabin) not having normal atmospheric pressure maintained at a high altitude
shortDefinitions: (of aircraft cabin) not having normal atmospheric pressure maintained at high altitude
